article.headline: Polk, Adefeso notch double-doubles
article.linkText: Fiesta Bowl Classic: No. 25 Arizona beats American
article.story:
TUCSON, Arizona (Ticker) -- Shawntinice Polk and Danielle 
Adefeso both recorded a double-double to lead No. 25 Arizona
over American University, 75-63, and tie a school record with
its 15th straight win at home.

Polk, who notched her second double-double of the season, scored
18 points and grabbed 10 rebounds.  The 6-5 center also blocked
six shots and handed out five assists.

Adefeso, a junior, came off the bench to record a career-high 13
points and 10 rebounds for the Wildcats (4-2), who will face
the University of Massachusetts in the championship game of the
Fiesta Bowl Classic on Sunday.

Dee-Dee Wheeler netted 17 points and Aimee Grzyb chipped in with
five assists for Arizona, which shot 52 percent from the field
in the second half to open up a seven-point contest.

Angel Jordan had 14 points and Chanel Hunt added a double-double
of 13 points and 11 boards for the Eagles (3-2), who committed
24 turnovers in the loss.
